Nigeria forward Samuel Kalu, who collapsed during training last week due to severe dehydration. The Bordeaux player was rushed to hospital Friday suffering from severe dehydration due to severe heat. Temperatures expected to hover between 35 and 38 Celsius (95-100.4 Fahrenheit) over the next month in Egypt. He missed Nigeria's 1-0 win over Burundi on Saturday in the opening match in Group B in Alexandria.